How rising AI workloads, advanced chip architectures and new fabs are feeding into Lam Research's etch and deposition tool demand assumptions.
What analysts are building in for revenue growth, margin expansion and earnings by 2029, including differing views between the most bullish and most cautious forecasts.
Key risks around China exposure, customer concentration, wafer fab equipment cyclicality, competition and the ongoing R&D spending needed to support new process technologies.
